   DRUGS-SPORTS (Undated) _ Doping scandals have become so
commonplace in international sports that fewer and fewer people
trust either the athletes or the officials charged with guarding
against cheating. Many athletes, coaches, administrators and
scientists say that these sports have become so disfigured by
doubts, anger and fatalism over the question of cheating through
drug use that a widespread cynicism about sport's basic integrity
has taken hold. By Jere Longman. (3300 words)
