</P>
<P>
   Notable: Kansas City has won the last three in the series,
including a 28-8 rout in the first game of the season. . . .
Oakland WR Tim Brown has 41 catches and 557 yards in his last six
games against the Chiefs. . . . Raiders DE Lance Johnstone and DT
Darrell Russell are the league's only tandem with double-digit
sacks. . . . In his last five games, Chiefs WR Derrick Alexander
has 28 catches for 507 yards. . . . Kansas City RB Bam Morris is
starting and has six touchdowns in his last five games.
</P>
