regular-season games and needs 12 points to break the NFL scoring
record. . . . Despite a broken left hand, Vikings QB Randall
Cunningham is expected to play, and he leads the league with a
107.3 passer rating. . . . PK Gary Anderson needs eight points to
set a record for most points without a touchdown. . . . In his last
two games, Oilers QB Steve McNair has 495 passing yards and 139
rushing yards. . . . Tennessee WR Yancey Thigpen had 10 catches in
his last game against the Vikings.
</P>
<P>
   Favorite: Minnesota by 8.
</P>
