<P>
   RUSSIA-GOLD _ PETROPAVLOVSK-KAMCHATSKY, Russia _ Desperately low
on fuel to run its power plants and short of food to feed its
people, this region suffers grim hardships facing much of Russia
amid an economic crisis and a cruel winter season. What's a poor
Russian region far away from Moscow to do? There's gold in them
there hills. Embedded in the pristine, snow-capped mountains of the
Kamchatka peninsula in Russia's Far East is a fortune in gold,
platinum, silver and other minerals. (Holmes, Cox News Service).
