<P>
   LA-NINA (Los Angeles) _ El Nino's rogue sister La Nina has left
Los Angeles with half as much rain as normal so far this winter and
caused wild temperature swings, including a roller coaster of
record low and high temperatures, weather experts say. La Nina, a
global weather pattern caused by unusually cold equatorial waters,
has meant drier weather for Southern California, in sharp contrast
to the cold, wet weather last winter that was served up by the
century's most potent El Nino. By Doug Haberman. (Will move in the
``n'' California and ``a'' national news files.)
